text: Leonel Cárdenas, also known as Leonel Cárdenas Mora, also spelled Cárdenas (born 8 February 2000 in Tlalnepantla de Baz) is a Mexican professional squash player. As of February 2018, he was ranked number 145 in the world. In 2017 he won the Country Club Cochabamba Bolivia Open professional PSA tournament. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican male squash players
